commit.message:
Remove wasm-opt stage from dockerfile

wasm-pack runs wasm-opt on the resulting wasm bundle. Running it again
in the dockerfile didn't yield any improvements
Build dockerfile with proper asset digestion

Rework with web worker

Using a web worker allows the expensive network parsing to not occur on
the UI thread -- instead communicate via message passing. This also
allowed for a more fine grained control over loading the wasm bundle. In
the future a better error message can be displayed when loading the
bundle.

Reduce wasm bundle size

Through a combination of llvm optimizing for size and wasm-opt from
binaryen. The wasm file shrunk from 670KB to 470KB.

Fix docker build with incomplete wasm artifact

Only the dependencies were compiled into wasm. This resulted in a tiny
wasm bundle, so add a test to count how many bytes are present
Dockerfile: split dependencies and build stage for caching
